        "action": "Review of C1 Licence Medical Standards for drivers with epilepsy",
        "additional_details": "We call on the Government to conduct a review of this, as we believe the current rules exclude many with well managed epilepsy from transport and emergency service careers.\r\n\r\nWe think the evidence shows the risks can be managed safely with medical oversight.",
        "background": "Currently, drivers with epilepsy need to have been seizure free for 10 years without medication to drive vehicles covered by a C1 license. ",
